laboratory_examinations.findings: Diffuse inflammation of the appendix and mural hyperemia with subjacent fat stranding, with the appendix measuring up to 7 mm in diameter, consistent with acute appendicitis. No free air or periappendiceal abscess. Normal findings for liver, gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, kidneys, small and large bowel loops, bladder, prostate, and rectum.
